{"source_key":"sha256-9b0f9c3f961abf38b897cbefe7e9ac46","record_index":69,"record_hash":"sha256:81d1fa7153b30ea9186c735b635a4a28abad1be1a6b5c67978ca3188184855b5","timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:50:22.489Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: a76d7c\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 997\nOutput:\n     1\t# Agent Session Capture\n     2\t\n     3\tThis directory describes the GitButler proof of concept for capturing AI coding\n     4\tsession metadata into GitMeta, plus future ideas that are intentionally out of\n     5\tscope for the first patch.\n     6\t\n     7\tBefore using this as a coding-agent prompt, run it through the review loop in\n     8\t[Spec Iteration Process](spec-iteration-process.md). For the first actual patch,\n     9\t[First POC Implementation Contract](first-poc-implementation.md) is the source of\n    10\ttruth.\n    11\t\n    12\t## POC Shape\n    13\t\n    14\tThe first milestone should be deliberately boring and explicit:\n    15\t\n    16\t- `crates/but-agentlog` owns agent log capture behavior\n    17\t- the GitButler CLI exposes hidden, feature-gated `agentlog capture`,\n    18\t  `agentlog hook`, and `agentlog sync` commands\n    19\t- the first implementation captures Codex or Claude data from an explicit\n    20\t  transcript path\n    21\t- provenance and dedupe data is written to shareable-ready `gitbutler:*` GitMeta\n    22\t  keys on the `project` target\n    23\t- capture can optionally associate that project session with an explicit GitMeta\n    24\t  target\n    25\t- hooks can capture from Claude Code or Codex lifecycle payloads that include an\n    26\t  exact transcript path\n    27\t- transcript records are always captured and redacted before storage\n    28\t- no background watcher or broad machine scan\n    29\t- sync is explicit and uses GitMeta's configured metadata remote behavior\n    30\t\n    31\tThe data shape is intentionally pointed at two later product flows:\n    32\t\n    33\t- handoff, where a session captured on one machine can later be read from GitMeta\n    34\t  and resumed on another machine or by another agent\n    35\t- review sharing, where a branch or pull request can later reference one or more\n    36\t  project sessions for a GitButler web timeline\n    37\t\n    38\tThose flows are why the POC uses durable project sessions plus future\n    39\trelationship keys, rather than storing transcript data directly on a branch or\n    40\tinside `meta:local:*`.\n    41\t\n    42\tA good first command shape is:\n    43\t\n    44\t```text\n    45\tbut agentlog capture \\\n    46\t  --transcript-path <path> \\\n    47\t  [--agent codex|claude] \\\n    48\t  [--associate-target <target>]\n    49\t\n    50\tbut agentlog hook \\\n    51\t  [--agent codex|claude] \\\n    52\t  [--associate-target <target>]\n    53\t\n    54\tbut agentlog sync\n    55\t```\n    56\t\n    57\t## Design Bias\n    58\t\n    59\tPrefer safety and auditability over clever discovery. It is better for the POC\n    60\tto capture nothing unless given an exact transcript than to accidentally capture\n    61\tthe wrong or private session.\n    62\t\n    63\t## Documents\n    64\t\n    65\t- [Spec Iteration Process](spec-iteration-process.md)\n    66\t- [First POC Implementation Contract](first-poc-implementation.md)\n    67\t- [Requirements and Goals](requirements-and-goals.md)\n    68\t- [Architecture](architecture.md)\n    69\t- [GitMeta Data Model](gitmeta-data-model.md)\n    70\t- [Agentlog Sync Lifecycle](agentlog-sync-lifecycle.md)\n    71\t- [Future Use Cases](future-use-cases.md)\n    72\t- [Capture Workflow](capture-workflow.md)\n    73\t- [Agentlog Maintainability Playbook](maintainability-playbook.md)\n    74\t\n    75\t## Reference Material\n    76\t\n    77\t- [GitMeta specification](https://git-meta.com/spec/)\n    78\t- [GitMeta targets and keys](https://git-meta.com/spec/exchange-format/targets.html)\n    79\t- [GitMeta list values](https://git-meta.[REDACTED:entropy].html)\n    80\t- [GitMeta standard keys](https://git-meta.com/spec/implementation/standard-keys.html)\n    81\t- [GitMeta workflow guidance](https://git-meta.com/spec/implementation/workflow.html)\n    82\t- [Claude Code sessions](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/sessions)\n    83\t- [How Claude Code works](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/how-claude-code-works)\n    84\t- [Claude Code agent SDK sessions](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/sessions)\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T19:50:22.489Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}